<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">271. Burris-Meyer, Elizabeth. Color and Design in the Decorative Arts. NewYork: Prentice-Hall, 1935. 572 pp. Index, bibl., B/W illus., color illus. </p><p class="annot">This how-to approach to color harmony in dress and retailingpresents color principles and theory as well as design principles. Much of the information is now dated, but this book is interesting for its historical perspective on the teaching of color in an applied design format. A classic of its type, it is frequently cited in bibliographies for that reason. </p></div>
